node.text:
celebrating earth day with a plant-forward salad featuring sweet potato fries (salad fries: iykyk 🍟), ranch kale, and a crispy cauliflower burger! 

one of my forever goals is to decrease my carbon footprint while increasing the nutrient load in my meals, which is why I keep @drpraegers in my freezer as a meatless options that’s fast and flavorful. 👌🏻😌 they just launched their cauliflower burger, which is loaded with all the good stuff: 9 grams of plant-based protein, 6 different vegetables, and 9 grams of whole foods-sourced fiber. the burgers are also gluten-free, grain-free, and non-gmo! 

dr. praeger’s is donating a percentage of sales to an organization called farmers against hunger 🌾, which bridges the gap between the agriculture industry and hunger relief organizations. ♥️ combatting food insecurity is a huge passion of mine, which makes me love this launch that much more. 

click the link in my profile to check out the new cauliflower burger or find them in the freezer aisle at your local grocery store. use my code HAVEN5 for $5 off your order! #sponsored #drpraegerspartner

node.text:
Feeling full-on fall cozying up to a big bowl of PUMPKIN CHILI! 🥰🎃 This one comes together in under 20 minutes, thanks to the instant pot (although a slow cooker or stove top can be used if you prefer), and is packed with warming spices, hearty vegetables, and silky pumpkin purée, which adds amazing full-bodied flavor and texture. 👌🏻Toppings: add your favorites! I went with cheddar cheese, greek yogurt, and cilantro — all optional, but all encouraged. 👏🏻 
-
I also used @purefarmland plant-based protein starters and @betterthanbouillon organic seasoned vegetable base in this recipe — 100% plant-based products which have made it easy for me to incorporate more environmentally-friendly meals into my diet without sacrificing flavor ☺️🌍 🌱. Reducing my carbon footprint has been one of my goals this year and these products make it easier to do it 🧡. 
-
Be sure to check out the post on @purefarmland’s feed for the opportunity to enter an exciting giveaway —  you could have the chance to win $500 PLUS a variety of products from @purefarmland and @betterthanbouillon to recreate this chili recipe!Hope you enjoy it as much as we have! 😘
#PFfam #ad #betterthanbouillon
-
HEALTHY INSTANT POT PUMPKIN CHILI

1 T. olive oil
1 cup onion, chopped
1 green bell pepper, chopped
3 cloves garlic
1 pound Simply Seasoned Pure Farmland Protein Starter
1 (14oz) can diced tomatoes
1 (14oz) can pumpkin
1 (14oz) can kidney beans (drained)
1 (14oz) can white beans (drained)
2 T chili powder
1 tsp smoked paprika
1 tsp cumin
¼ tsp dried oregano
1 tsp Better Than Bouillon Seasoned Vegetable Base (dissolved in 8 oz boiling water) 

Optional Toppings:
Greek yogurt or sour cream, cilantro, grated cheese, avocado

1.In the saute mode,  cook onion, green pepper, and olive oil for 5 minutes.
2. Add garlic and Farmland Protein Starter. Break up with a spoon and saute 5 min.
3. Add all remaining ingredients to the instant pot. Cook on high pressure for 15 minutes before releasing pressure.

node.text: Long-term and sustainable change is usually the product of incremental changes. Navigating our roles — and assessing our impact — in the Black Lives Matter movement may feel overwhelming, but it doesn’t have to be. Making small, gradual changes will increase the likelihood that those changes are impactful and long-lasting.

node.text:
Celebrating Cinco de Mayo with some sheet pan BBQ chicken zucchini chip nachooss 🌮. These have quickly become a quarantine happy hour staple — especially when served with a round of margs, which is definitely the move we’re making tonight! 🍹💃🏼
-
I like using equal parts tortilla chips and zucchini ‘chips,’ but if you’re looking to sneak in a couple extra veggie servings, go all parts zucchini! The beauty of nachos is that they’re totally customizable and can be topped with whatever you have on hand.
-
BBQ CHICKEN ZUCCHINI NACHOS 
1/2 bag tortilla chips (I usually use a grain-free cassava chip, but any works
2-3 zucchini, sliced 
Avocado or olive oil spray
1-2 cups shredded chicken breast 
1/2 cup @primalkitchenfoods Mango Jalapeño BBQ sauce (this *MAKES* the nachos)
1/2 cup pinto beans or black beans
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese 
1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, sliced
1/4 cup red onion, diced 
1/2 cup avocado, cubed 
1/4 cup sour cream or greek yogurt 
1/4 cup cilantro, chopped -
See IGTV video for directions! And bonus: use code SARA10 for a discount on your favorite Primal Kitchen products at primalkitchen.com 🎉🥳 My faves are their BBQ sauces, avocado oil mayos (they have a new pesto one that’s 👌🏻), and creamy dressings!

node.text:
Pretty sure my quarantine diet is pushing 99% cookies, pizza, and banana bread at this point 🤣. Maintaining those ratios means baking multiple batches of these cookies (exhibit A: me yesterday) and ordering takeout 🍕 tonight (exhibit B: me counting down the hours till dinner). What are your weekend plans? I think these cookies should be apart of them 👏🏻. HAPPY FRIDAY! ❤️
-
FLOURLESS PEANUT BUTTER CHOCOLATE CHIP COOKIES

1 cup peanut butter 
3/4 cup coconut sugar, white sugar, or swerve granular (for low sugar/keto option)
1 egg
1/2 teaspoon baking soda 
1/4 teaspoon salt 
1 cup chocolate chips 
Preheat oven to 350 F. In a bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips. Stir to combine and then gently fold in chips. Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place in a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Dot with additional chocolate chips and bake ~10-12 minutes.

node.text:
one pan creamy spinach & artichoke pasta!✨🍃🤩 took a favorite dip and turned it into a favorite noodle night featuring heart of palm linguine. sooo what we have here is basically a skillet of saucy veggies + chicken awaiting your next couch + cozies situation. no heart of palm pasta? no prob: substitute spaghetti squash, spaghetti, or whatever you have on hand.

garlic bread: optional, but not really because you’re gonna need it to sop up all that extra saauwce! enjoy 🥖😘
-
CREAMY SPINACH & ARTICHOKE DIP PASTA SKILLET
serve 2. substitute spaghetti squash or regular noodles for the heart of palm pasta if you don’t have any on hand. 

1 (9 oz) box pre-cooked hearts of palm pasta OR 2 cups cooked pasta of choice • 1 cup dairy-free garlic cheese sauce (recipe linked in profile) • 1 chicken breast, grilled and sliced into 1/2-inch pieces • 1/2 cup chopped artichoke hearts, drained • 2 garlic cloves, minced • 2 teaspoons olive oil • 3 cups fresh spinach • 1/4 cup parmesan cheese 

1)heat a large skillet for ~1 minute over medium-high heat. Add garlic cloves and sauté for 2-3 minutes; add spinach and sauté an additional 30 seconds or until wilted; stir in artichoke hearts. 2) drain heart of palm pasta and add it to the skillet: stir. add creamy garlic cheese sauce and cook until bubbly. stir in parmesan cheese and cook an additional minute or until cheese is melted.

node.text:
peanut butter honey walnut banana bread! ✨🍯🍌 I’ve made maaaany loaves of b bread and this one…this oooone! is my 10/10 tried and true best. 

irresistibly soft, fluffy, moist (love the texture, not the word), and packed with wholesome ingredients like coconut oil, ripe bananas, and heart-healthy walnuts 🙌🏻 you and your monday want it need it gotta have it. 😘 

PEANUT BUTTER HONEY WALNUT BANANA BREAD 
• grain-free • gluten free • paleo-adaptable •

2 large overripe bananas • 1/4 cup coconut oil • 1/4 cup creamy peanut butter • 2 tbsp. honey • 1 tsp. vanilla • 2 eggs • 1/4 cup almond flour • 1/4 cup coconut flour • 1/2 tsp baking soda • 1/2 tsp baking powder • 1/2 tsp salt • 1/2 tsp cinnamon • 1/2 cup chopped walnuts 

1) preheat oven to 350F. grease an 8” loaf pan (or, alternatively, line it with parchment paper). 2) In a small bowl, combine coconut flour, almond flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon; set aside 3) In a large bowl, melt coconut oil and peanut butter in a microwave, approx. 1 minute). add mashed bananas, honey, vanilla, and eggs; mix well. 4) stir dry ingredients into wet until well combined. 6) pour batter into prepared pan and bake 30-40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.

lemon garlic butter baked salmon w/asparagus, and crispy potatooess! this one’s fresh, fast, flavorful, and feels a leeetle bit fancy without the fuss because it comes with just one pan to clean 🤩🙌🏻 prep ahead for weekday lunches at the office or weekend picnics in the park. 🧺 

wrapping up a whirlwind day cozied on the couch with a glass of wine in hand and a passed out puppy in lap. hope you had a good one and happy almost friday! 😘 

LEMON GARLIC BUTTER BAKED SALMON WITH CRISPY POTATOES & ASPARAGUS

potatoes: preheat oven to 400 F. toss 1 pound quartered yukon golds in 1 tablespoon olive oil; season with salt and pepper 2) arrange potatoes on a large baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes; remove from oven

salmon + asparagus: while the potatoes are roasting, combine 3 tablespoons garlic ghee (or butter) + 2 cloves minced garlic + a splash of lemon juice in a small bowl; microwave for 30 seconds, or until melted. season four (4-6 oz) salmon filets and 1 lb. asparagus with sea salt + black pepper. once the potatoes have been removed from the oven, push them to one side of the baking sheet (they’re not finished cooking yet), and arrange salmon and asparagus as seen in the photo. drizzle with lemon garlic butter sauce. bake for 10-15 minutes or until salmon is cooked through. remove from oven and turn it to broil. broil for 5 minutes or until salmon, potatoes, and asparagus are crispy. enjoy! ❤️

node.text:
embracing salad season with open arms and a big bowl of cool n’ creamy garlic-avocado ranch pasta 🙌🏻🥑🍅😎 because hot weather calls for cooold noodles. 

this pasta salad is super versatile and just as easy to adjust as your thermostat. 

no arugula? no problem! omit it and toss in whichever greens you have on hand. vegetarian? say bubbye to bacon and toss in sundried tomatoes for extra flavor. 👌🏻the only non-negotiables here are hearty noodles (I like chickpea) and a quality bottle of ranch dressing (see my suggestions below). here’s what you’ll need:

CREAMY AVOCADO-GARLIC RANCH PASTA SALAD 
2 cups cooked chickpea pasta (I like shells for this recipe)
1/4 cup @organicgirl white cheddar ranch dressing** (this is sold at whole foods and can be found in the refrigerator near the produce)
1/2 cup sliced avocado
1/2 cup sliced cherry tomatoes
2 cups arugula
2 tablespoons red onion, chopped
2 slices cooked nitrite-free bacon, crumbled (optional)
1/4 teaspoon garlic powder (optional)

** other dressing suggestions: primal kitchen avocado oil ranch // sir kensington’s ranch 

toss cooled pasta with dressing and then stir in remaining ingredients. that’s it! this can be prepped ahead and keeps for 1-2 days in the fridge. if you meal prep ahead, I suggest adding the avocado shortly before serving, OR tossing it with lemon juice, to prevent it from turning brown.

node.text:
my monday could use a flourless peanut butter blondie or twooo, how boutchu? 🥜🍫🤩 these ooey gooeys are the easiest 6-ingredient snack and can be adapted for paleo or vegan if that’s your thing. my thing? practicing self care in the form of simplicity + chocolate. 💁🏼‍♀️ here’s what you need:

1 cup creamy peanut butter
2 eggs
1/3 cup honey
1/2 tsp. baking soda 
2 tbsp. peanut flour 
1/2 cup chocolate chips 

1. combine all ingredients except chocolate chips in a medium-size bowl; mix until smooth. fold in chocolate chips and pour into an 8x8-inch baking dish lined with parchment paper. dot the tops with extra chocolate chips (optional) and bake at 350 F. for 20-25 minutes, or until slightly golden.

* substitute almond, cashew, or sunflower butter for peanut butter 
** substitute flax eggs
*** substitute brown sugar or coconut sugar but increase quantity to 1/2 cup

they’re heeere! the easiest CRISPY AIR FRYER CRAB CAKES for those moments you wanna be at the beach but you gotta bring the beach to you. 🦀🐚💁🏼‍♀️

I’m no marylander, but I love a good crab cake and also love any easy recipe that can be thrown together in under 30 minutes on a weeknight. 🤌🏻 these are all of that and so much more because they utilize the air fryer, which halves the cooking time (and the grease!) 

serve with creamy cauliflower mash and grilled asparagus - or whichever savory side your heart desires. xx 😘 

CRISPY AIR FRYER CRAB CAKES
(grain-free • gluten-free • paleo • keto)

1 egg • 3 tbsp. avocado oil mayonnaise (or greek yogurt) • 4 tsp. lemon juice • 1/8 tsp red pepper flakes • 1 tsp dried tarragon • 1 tbsp. minced green onions • 8 ounces lump crabmeat (fresh or canned) • 1/2 cup crushed almond flour crackers (I used @realphatfoods)

 1) in a medium bowl, whisk together egg, mayo, lemon juice, red pepper flakes, tarragon, and green onions 2) gently stir in crabmeat, then add cracker crumbs 3) place  lin air fryer basket and lightly spray tops with avocado oil 4) air fry at 370 degrees for 10 minutes.

✨ creamy zucchini mac n’ cheese! ✨  this is a big bowl of seasonal summer comfort food that comes together quick and packs several sneaky(ish) veggie servings 🙌🏻🥰🌱 no need for a side salad — just  bowl it up and cozy up on the couch. dinner: done and done! 🤌🏻

CREAMY ZUCCHINI  MAC N’ CHEESE 
(serves 2). the creamy cheddar ‘caulifredo’ sauce (cauliflower-based alfredo) can be made dairy-free/vegan with a few simple swaps! 

2 cups cooked chickpea pasta shells (or noodle of choice — regular/keto etc) • 2 cups shredded zucchini • 1 cup creamy cheddar caulifredo sauce 

simply toss hot pasta with the sauce and shredded zucchini. the zucchini “cooks” and absorbs the creamy/cheesy flavors as it’s warmed by the sauce.

for the cheddar caulifredo: 
(makes ~2 cups)

4 garlic cloves • 3 cups cauliflower florets • 1/2 teaspoon salt • 1/2 cup broth (chicken or vegetable) • 1/4 teaspoon pepper • 1 tablespoon butter or ghee (vegan can be substituted) • 1 cup cheddar (or cheese of choice — dairy or vegan)

1. steam cauliflower and cauliflower in a steamed basket until tender. transfer to a blender or food processor while still hot and add remaining ingredients; blend until smooth, about 2 minutes. pour sauce into a medium-size sauce pan and heat over low; stir in cheese and stir until incorporated.

node.text:
happy 4th!! 🇺🇸 this STRAWBERRY SNACK CAKE is here to keep cravings at bay morning, noon, and night, and is just as appropriate for picnics + potlucks as it is for slow sunday mornings with a cup of coffee (x’s twooo) close by. 🥰 gluten-free, grain-free, and texturally half parts shortcake, half parts pound cake, and full parts july 4th because it’s berry season, babyyy. 🍓hope you love it and cheers to a safe and healthy holiday! 🎇😘 

STRAWBERRY SNACK CAKE
(gluten-free • grain-free • keto option)

3 cups fine-ground almond flour (no substitutions) • 1/4 cup vanilla or plain protein powder (this is *optional*) • 2 teaspoons baking powder • ½ teaspoon salt • 6 tablespoons coconut oil, melted (or butter, softened)  • 2 tablespoons unsweetened applesauce • 2/3 cup coconut sugar (sub Swerve granular for low carb/keto) • 3 large eggs • 1/4 teaspoon lemon extract (optional, but lemon enhances the strawberry flavor) • 1/2 teaspoon vanilla • 2/3 cup water (or almond milk) • 1 cup chopped strawberries 

1. preheat oven to 325 F. grease an 8x8-inch pan with coconut oil or cooking spray OR line it with parchment paper. 2) in a medium bowl, whisk together the almond flour, protein powder, (if using), baking powder, and salt. set aside. 3) in a large bowl, beat the coconut oil (or butter), applesauce, and sugar (or sweetener) until well combined. beat in the eggs, lemon extract, and vanilla extract. 4) add the dry ingredients to the wet and stir in water; beat until combined. stir in chopped strawberries. spread the batter into the prepared pan and smooth the top. sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on top for a crunchy top! (optional) 5) bake 30 to 40 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and a toothpick comes out clean.

node.text:
heading into the long weekend thinking about bbqs and BBQ CHICKEN PIZZA 🤩🍕 this saucy slice is everything I want in a summer friday: a little bit sweet, a little bit spicy, and casual enough to eat on a  couch.

the crust is made with spaghetti squash (!!) and proves that veggie crusts really can taste good. you know how cauliflower crust can be super soggy? yeah, same. spaghetti squash is starchier and sturdier than cauliflower, yielding a far thicker and crispier crust. 

not on the 100% homemade train? you can swap a store bought crust and 100% give yourself more time for wine + cozy time, which is 100% the move I’m making tonight. 🙋🏼‍♀️ happy holiday weekending!! ♥️

BBQ CHICKEN SPAGHETTI SQUASH CRUST PIZZA 
1 spaghetti squash crust (recipe below!)• 1/2 cup + jarred bbq sauce, divided • 1 large fully cooked chicken breast (about 8 oz), chopped • 1 cup smoked mozzarella, shredded* • 1/2 cup red onion, thinly sliced • 1/4 cup cilantro leaves, chopped 
-
SPAGHETTI SQUASH CRUST
(feel free food swap cheeses/seasonings with your favorites)
2 cups cooked spaghetti squash, separated into strands • 1 egg • 1 1/3 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded and divided • 1.5 teaspoons italian seasoning • 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder • 1/4 teaspoon salt • 4 tablespoons almond flour • 2 tablespoons parmesan cheese, shredded •

1. preheat oven to 450 F. line baking sheet with parchment paper and spray with cooking spray. 2) chop spaghetti squash into 1-inch pieces, and, working in small batches, wring dry using a tea towel until you have 1 cup. 3) place squash in a  large bowl and add egg, 1/3 cup mozzarella, almond flour, and seasonings; mix until well combined. 4) dump mixture onto prepared baking sheet and spread into a circle or oval shape that is 1/4-inch thick. bake for ~12-15 minutes, or until slightly firm. using hands, carefully flip the crust and add bbq chicken toppings. bake 8-10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly. cut and serve!
